---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Barley Trading from Russia & Ukraine | Buyer Access — AL Farhan General Trading Co."
  description="Buyer-focused barley trading from Russia and Ukraine to Middle East and Africa. Structured market access for international buyers."
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  locale="en"
  currentPath="commodities/barley"
>
  <!-- [1] HERO -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Bulk Barley Trading & Buyer Access</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Structured buyer access to bulk barley trading across Russia and Ukraine, serving Middle East and African markets.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-slate-800">Request Buyer Access</a>
      <a href="#trade-routes" class="rounded border border-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50">View Trade Routes</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- [2] INTRO — COMMODITY POSITIONING -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Buyer-Focused Barley Trading</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      AL Farhan General Trading Co. operates as a buyer-oriented trading intermediary, supporting international buyers engaged in bulk barley trade across Russian and Ukrainian markets.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Engagement is structured around market access, coordination, and trade clarity—without inventory ownership, production claims, or exclusivity representation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [3] BARLEY CATEGORIES — MARKET CONTEXT -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Barley Categories Commonly Traded</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Bulk barley trading typically involves the following market categories, depending on application and destination requirements:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-900">Feed Barley</strong><br />
        Utilized within animal feed production across agricultural and industrial supply chains.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-slate-900">Malting Barley</strong><br />
        Applied in brewing and malt-based industries where specifications align.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      Categories are provided for market orientation only.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [4] MARKET ACCESS — RUSSIA & UKRAINE ONLY -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Active Barley Trading Markets</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Barley trade engagement under this category is oriented exclusively toward the Russian and Ukrainian markets, subject to specification alignment and destination requirements.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      Market references are indicative and do not imply ownership, exclusivity, or direct sourcing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [5] TRADE ROUTES — DESTINATION-SPECIFIC -->
  <section id="trade-routes" class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Indicative Trade Routes for Barley</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>Russia → Middle East</li>
      <li>Ukraine → Middle East</li>
      <li>Russia → Africa</li>
      <li>Ukraine → Africa</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      Routes are indicative and structured per buyer destination and logistical alignment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [6] HOW BUYER ENGAGEMENT WORKS -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">How Buyer Engagement Works</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-slate-600">
      <li>Buyer inquiry and barley category alignment</li>
      <li>Market orientation and trade framework discussion</li>
      <li>Structured communication and documentation</li>
      <li>Controlled facilitation through defined trade logic</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
      No pricing, guarantees, or inventory representations are displayed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [7] COMPLIANCE & CLARITY -->
  <section id="compliance" class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Clear, Buyer-Oriented Trade Framework</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
      All barley-related engagements are positioned within a clarity-first framework suitable for institutional review, procurement workflows, and compliance evaluation.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="text-slate-600 underline hover:text-slate-900">View Compliance & KYC →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- [8] FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Proceed with Structured Barley Trade Engagement</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-slate-800">Request Buyer Access</a>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="rounded border border-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50">Contact Our Team</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
